23/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The 5th European Ministerial Conference on Equality Between Women and Men opened Wednesday (22 January) in Skopje. 
The event, organised by the Council of Europe (CoE) in co-operation with the Macedonian Ministry of Labour and Social Policy, brought together representatives of government, the international community and NGOs from the 39 CoE member states. 
Participants are expected to adopt a declaration on the role of women in democracy building and their contribution to the rebuilding of post-conflict societies. 
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 22/01/03)
